[No. 10,564. Department Two.] PEOPLE v. HAN TIN. Municipal Ordinance—Constitutional Law. Appeal from a judgment of conviction, and an order denying a new trial, in the Superior Court of the County of San Joaquin. Buckley, J.

McStay & Swinnerton, for Appellant.

George A. Blanchard for the Attorney-General, for Respondent.

The Court:

Upon the authority of the People v. Car Soy, ante, p. 102, judgment and order reversed, and cause remanded for a new trial.
